cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new class of graph automata that recognize graph languages definable in monadic second-order logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper is inspired by distributed algorithms and introduces a new class of automata for graphs. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with monadic second-order logic. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the expressive power of different variants of the proposed automata. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new type of automata that can be seen as a generalization of finite automata to graphs.
